CAPE TOWN &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s competition watchdog has granted Barclays Africa conditional immunity from prosecution in return for its continuing cooperation in the rand currency rigging probe, the head of Competition Commission said on Tuesday.&#8220;We have a conditional agreement with them on immunity but this is subject to confirmation depending on the extent of their cooperation,&#8221; Tembinkosi Bonakele told a committee meeting of parliament on Tuesday. More to follow.